  "examTip": "8255A is a 40-pin DIP Programmable Peripheral Interface. It has 3 I/O ports: Port A (PA0-PA7), Port B (PB0-PB7), and Port C (PC0-PC7). Address lines A0 and A1 select the port or control register. RD̄ and WR̄ control read/write. CS̄ is the active-low chip select. RESET clears all ports to input mode. D0-D7 is the data bus connecting to the 8085 system data bus.",
