  "theory": "The Intel 8255A is a general-purpose Programmable Peripheral Interface (PPI) IC used with 8-bit microprocessors such as the 8085 and 8086. It provides 24 I/O lines organized as three 8-bit ports (A, B, C) and interfaces the CPU to various peripheral devices.\n\nPin Groupings:\n- Port A (PA0-PA7) — Pins 4,3,2,1 (left) and 40,39,38,37 (right): 8-bit bidirectional data port. Mode 0, 1, or 2 selectable via Control Word Register.\n- Port B (PB0-PB7) — Pins 18,19,20 (left) and 21,22,23,24,25 (right): 8-bit bidirectional data port. Mode 0 or 1 selectable.\n- Port C (PC0-PC7) — Pins 14-17 (PC0-PC3 lower group, left) and 10-13 (PC4-PC7 upper group, left): 8-bit port used for I/O or handshaking signals in Modes 1 and 2.\n- Data Bus (D0-D7) — Pins 34-27 (right): Bidirectional data bus connecting to the 8085/8086 system data bus.\n- Control Signals (left side):\n  - RD̄ (Pin 5): Active-low read. When low, CPU reads from a selected 8255A port.\n  - WR̄ (Pin 36): Active-low write. When low, CPU writes to a selected port or the Control Word Register.\n  - CS̄ (Pin 6): Active-low chip select. Must be low for any operation.\n  - RESET (Pin 35): Active-high reset. Clears the Control Word Register and sets all ports to input mode.\n- Address Lines (A0, A1) — Pins 9 and 8:\n  - A1=0, A0=0: Port A selected\n  - A1=0, A0=1: Port B selected\n  - A1=1, A0=0: Port C selected\n  - A1=1, A0=1: Control Word Register selected\n- Power: VCC (+5V) at Pin 26, GND at Pin 7.\n\nOperating Modes:\n- Mode 0 (Basic I/O): Simple input or output on all three ports independently.\n- Mode 1 (Strobed I/O): Port A or Port B with handshaking, using Port C bits as control/status.\n- Mode 2 (Bidirectional Bus): Only Port A supports this; 8-bit bidirectional with handshaking.",
  "keyPoints": [
    "8255A provides 24 programmable I/O lines: Port A (PA0-PA7), Port B (PB0-PB7), Port C (PC0-PC7).",
    "A0 and A1 lines select which port or the Control Word Register (CWR) to read/write.",
    "CS̄ (Chip Select, active-low) must be asserted for any RD̄/WR̄ operation to affect the 8255A.",
    "RESET (active-high) forces all ports to Mode 0 Input mode — all pins become inputs.",
    "Port C is split: upper nibble (PC4-PC7) works with Port A; lower nibble (PC0-PC3) works with Port B.",
    "Mode 2 (Bidirectional Bus) is exclusively available on Port A only."
  ],
  "useCases": [
    "Interfacing keyboards, LED arrays, 7-segment displays, and printers to an 8085 system.",
    "ADC/DAC interfacing for data acquisition systems.",
    "Handshake-based peripheral control using Mode 1 strobed I/O."
  ]
